    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Logging On and Staying On</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Spielman letter says June 22 Q&amp;A column gave incomplete answer to the reader who was often disconnected while trying to download Web files; suggests disabling the antivirus program</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The answer to the reader who was often disconnected while trying to download Web files (''When Modems Fail to Stay Connected,'' Q &amp; A, June 22) is incomplete. I had that problem, and despite tinkering by I.S.P. tech support people, the culprit turned out to be Norton AntiVirus 2000. The moment I disabled it, I could download perfectly. So now I have to be careful what sites I download from.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL SPIELMAN  Bronx</p>
      </block>
